====================================================================================
JOIN-NECESSITY SWEEP — does any real k<=6 tiling need a >=3-generator (join) lattice?
test per lattice L:  s*(L)=min s s.t. wt<=s vectors GENERATE L (any count);
                     s*_pair(L)=min s s.t. a wt<=s unimodular PAIR (basis) exists.
JOIN NEEDED  <=>  s*_pair > s*   (generate but no 2 of them form a basis).
source: galebach.json oracle periods (k4-6 reference); zeta12->zeta24 embedding.
====================================================================================

[VERDICT LATTICE] t6649 (k6, snub-square band, lambda1=1.932):
    Gauss-basis weights=(2,7) -> basis vec of wt 7 is OUTSIDE the s*=6 pool
    s*=6  s*_pair=6  ->  JOIN NEEDED = False
    (weight-!=-length IS active here: 2nd min has wt 7, but u+v has wt 6 and still pairs to a basis)

[ROBUSTNESS] random sample of 14 k=6 oracle lattices (independent recompute):
    t6138: basis-wt=(2,12) s*=12 s*_pair=12
    t6583: basis-wt=(8,8) s*=8 s*_pair=8
    t6065: basis-wt=(3,5) s*=5 s*_pair=5
    t6262: basis-wt=(1,12) s*=12 s*_pair=12
    t6121: basis-wt=(2,12) s*=12 s*_pair=12
    t6508: basis-wt=(7,7) s*=7 s*_pair=7
    t6461: basis-wt=(5,5) s*=5 s*_pair=5
    t6484: basis-wt=(9,9) s*=9 s*_pair=9
    t6668: basis-wt=(6,6) s*=6 s*_pair=6
    t6389: basis-wt=(3,7) s*=7 s*_pair=7
    t6215: basis-wt=(6,6) s*=6 s*_pair=6
    t6097: basis-wt=(10,10) s*=10 s*_pair=10
    t6500: basis-wt=(7,7) s*=7 s*_pair=7
    t6030: basis-wt=(7,7) s*=7 s*_pair=7
    -> join-needed in sample: 0

[CATALOGUE VERDICT]
  Shortcut (proven): s*_pair>s* is possible ONLY if s* < max(wtU,wtV) [reduced basis is itself a pair].
  CSV scan of all 1,339 lattices (k=1..6): exactly ONE row has s* < basis-wt -> t6649.
  t6649 explicitly resolved above: s*_pair == s*  -> NO join needed.
  ==> Across the ENTIRE oracle catalogue k=1..6, ZERO tilings require a join. Pairs suffice everywhere.
  Caveat: reference periods for k>=4 are Galebach (not certified); octagon tilings not in the zeta12 set.
